## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for life.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers life-state visibility,
current-vs-historical distinction,
state transition display,
bounded update surfaces,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible life state must distinguish:
- current active state
- changed state under review
- restricted state
- historical state
- closed state

## validation_rules
- life identity/continuity basis must resolve
- state basis must resolve
- transition basis must be valid
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid continuity basis
- invalid state transition
- invalid historical merge
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish continuity basis,
current state,
historical state,
transition result,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- continuity-aware runtime is explicit
- current/historical separation is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
